reviews.text: Pleasant walk at shore and waiting hydrofoil to Kizi. Free wi-fi. Lot of locals spending time. Outside gym is near. Sculptures worth to see.
The embankment is a nice collection of sculptures with free wifi. The locals will walk and fish. Teens gather to use the free wifi. Very pleasant to relax and walk.

reviews.quote: Killing time on my way to Kizhi
reviews.text: Not a bad way to kill time whilst waiting for the Kizhi hydrofoil. The park is pleasant, the waterfront really nice and there was also free wifi in designated sections of the promenade.

It's one of the very few and by far the most relaxing place to visit in Petrozavodsk. Although the sculptures look somewhat "postnuclearwar" they may be fun (each has an author's idea behind it - may sure you find out before you go). It's not exactly a year-round place, as it may get very windy and cold. In summer though (especially at sunset) the scenery is breathtaking.

Walk along the lakeside, fun sculptures, quiet ( at least on a early Sunday morning) and then you'll come to the hydrofoil ticket buying spot. There are also some quick food and water buying kiosks, and of course the ubiquitous souvenir shops.

reviews.quote: A great place to relax and enjoy the scenery!
reviews.text: Beautiful area to walk, sit, relax, view the lake, and check your email (the Park and Embankment has 'free wi-fi' that works well)! The sculptures are very interesting to view. There are also some exercise machines that you can utilize for free. There was a heavy rainstorm when i visited, accompanied by wind, and i still enjoyed it; that should tell you something about how nice it is to see.

reviews.quote: Lovely park and promenade where you can see sculptures - gifts from the twin cities of Petrozavodsk
reviews.text: Park and Lake Onega embankment create vibe of freedom, space and beauty of the city on the shores of a huge lake
A must see if you are in the city, it has a fantastic view on Onega-lake. It is about 30 min walk from the train station to the pier, where you can book a ticket to a number of boat tours..
It's the best place in Ptz. At the Embankment you can have cool rest, see interesting presents from different sister-towns. You'll breath with fresh lake air. Bite some food.
Nice views over the lake and some interesting monuments along the way. popular spot even in bad weather.

reviews.text: We enjoyed a very iced walk with my wife. The view of this giant lake, half frozen with perfectly round shaped dishes of ice, made the view something magic. Cover up properly as the cold really bites there, but, believe me: it is very well worth it.

reviews.quote: Just walk along and enjoy the beauty and the magnificence of the lake.
reviews.text: I went to Kareliya for a week. My point of visiting it was to see the picturesque sceneries and feel the freshness and the calmness of the nature. Petrozavodsk is the capital but I wasn't impressed by its sights, but the only place i went every dawn was Naberezhnaya of Onega lake. You see, Kareliya is the place where you can observe changes if the nature from the Ice age. Great number of lakes, woods and big stones are surrounded you. You feel something like nostalgia. I can speak a lot about Naberezhnaya, but the main thing is that near it you feel freedom, excitement but calmness at one moment.

reviews.quote: A stroll along the Lake Onega
reviews.text: A stroll along the embankment is a great opportunity for experiencing the lake. The embankment is close to several hotels, is wheel-chair accessible and has several works of art on display.
We enjoyed the walk around the embankment - there are many monuments and the view is nice. The kids loved to run around here!
To my opinion, it's one of the most beautiful places in Petrozavodsk! It's a place where you can really have a good rest with your family or friends.

The statue of tsar Peter the Great
reviews.text: The statue is located near harbour where hydrofoils to Kizi are departing. Easy to find. Tsar Peter the Great was founder of Petrozavodsk.

This statue of Peter the Great, who was the founder of the city, is close to harbor and a little bit in a shade of the trees in the park. It is made of bronze and is standing on a colossal granite pedestal which is carved of local Carelian gray granite. It has been moved several times but is now settled down in its current location. Check out this attraction, it is awesome.
Not bad go early in the morning when less people are around... after all its just a statue. Its about a 15 minute walk from onega castle hotel
The monument is in a park close to the pier where the boats takes off to Valomo monastery. So take a few minutes to have a look.

A nice monument to Peter the Great in the Center of the City in a Park setting. It is a constant reminder of how people idolize Peter the Great! While in Petrozavodsk, it is a 'must see', quite impressive.

Nice to see the town reinforce its strong links to one of Russias most popular Tzars. It is only a statue, nothing really special about it but it is on the sefront and does represent an important historical element of the city. Some nice eateries nearby and a nice walk along the lake front. One star lost as there is a homeless gathering point nearby, its not kept very well and looks very messy.
In the middle of the city certainly very impressive. Traffic is very bad very hard to find a time when the roads were not congested to be able to get around to sightsee

attractions.title: Kizhi State Historical-Architectural and Ethnographic Memorial Museum Reserve

reviews.text: This place is a dream that came true... Gangs of carpenters worked tirelessly in the Karelian harsh weather in order to preserve the unique wooden buildings from all this region. In addition to the shocking size of houses and their internal organization you can find out about the way of living, crafts, etc.

Museum of wooden architecture preserves for us and descendants unique wooden churches, chapels and dwellings, as well as old Orthodox icons. If you have the opportunity to stay on the island a few days, you get an incredible feeling and a charge of vital energy for creativity

We took a boat from Petrozavodsk about midday. We would have liked to go earlier, but apparently there were no earlier tickets. The island is really a little treasure. Nice to see how the restoration prgresses and how it becomes more and more tourist-loved and tourist-friendly place. We liked the demonstartions of wood carving and traditional embroidery.

great historical side with beautiful wooden karelian buildings. situated on an island but with good fast boat service from petrovazovsk. food and drinks get be bought on island also souvenirs. the big church is fantastic and so are the old farm buildings some are hundreds of years old and all are from the local area of Karelia ( north Western Russia)
Everything was interesting! It's realy the place to visit to!

attractions.title: Sea Museum of The Polar Odysseus Club

reviews.quote: Great museum made with a lot of passion
reviews.text: We loved this museum a lot! We felt the passion with it the members of the Polar Odysseus Club created this museum and build their traditional wooden boats. We where impressed the see the boats and which adventures journeys they did with it. For an example sailing from Petrosavodsk across Russia to Black Sea and until Spain and Egypt. Our enthusiastic guide gave her best to explain us everything. Thanks a lot Daria! She did a great job to show us around. Unfortunately we don't speak Russian, so we couldn't ask all the specific questions about sailing we had. Also quite interesting to see their actual work on wooden boats and all the details on the ground of the museum related to sailing.

While my Russian skills are quiet limited, it was still the best tour I ever had (while being hold in Russian). Our guide was very enthusiastic and welcoming. The museum area is packed with all kind of boats and it absolutly fun to walk ound arand discover more.

It is designed by Alexander Postnikov. Inside of the church you can feel the silent and harmonically spirit with some older and also younger people sitting praying. Of course the behavior should also be worthy and for example photographing are not allowed inside. A small shop is where you can buy icons and religious stuff is available in the altar hall. The old icons are very beautiful so don’t miss this place.
